def: The male of the salmon. [Prov. Eng.] Wright.
A feldspar closely related to orthoclase, but triclinic. It ischiefly a silicate of sodium, potassium, and aluminium. Sp. gr., 2.57-- 2.60.
Uttering sighs; grieving; lamenting. "Sighing millions."Cowper.-- Sigh"ing*ly, adv.
The glycerin salt of ricinelaidic acid, obtained as a whitecrystalline waxy substance by treating castor oil with nitrous acid.
Having great tension, or exaggerated action. Dunglison.
In a slow manner; moderately; not rapidly; not early; notrashly; not readly; tardly.
A white amorphous or crystalline substance obtained by thepartial dehydration of mannite.
